1
00:01:24,125 --> 00:01:25,376
Here we go.

2
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:29,798
A-ri, please say
happy birthday to Young-do.

3
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:31,841
I hope you live a long life.

4
00:01:31,925 --> 00:01:35,136
Cut. Let's do it again.
That's usually for the elderly.

5
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:37,388
Happy birthday. Is that good?

6
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:40,225
Okay. Keep going.

7
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:46,064
Can you please stop dumping
your friend on the first floor?

8
00:01:46,147 --> 00:01:48,900
As you can see,
he's making our cafe look bad.

9
00:01:50,527 --> 00:01:51,861
She's talking about me.

10
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:53,321
Good for you.

11
00:01:53,404 --> 00:01:55,490
-Ha-neul, say something as well.
-Forget it.

12
00:01:55,573 --> 00:01:58,326
-Say something to Young-do.
-Eun-ha, let me.

13
00:01:58,409 --> 00:02:00,120
It's okay. Please move.

14
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:02,080
This is too heavy. I'll carry it.

15
00:02:02,163 --> 00:02:03,081
I'm really fine.

16
00:02:03,164 --> 00:02:05,333
She's fine. Just say something
to the camera.

17
00:02:05,416 --> 00:02:06,543
-Let me.
-I'm fine.

18
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:07,794
-Oh, no.
-Hey.

19
00:02:11,256 --> 00:02:13,341
-Oh, no.
-I'm sorry.

20
00:02:13,424 --> 00:02:16,261
Could you say something
to Young-do as well?

21
00:02:20,265 --> 00:02:21,099
I'm sorry.

22
00:02:22,058 --> 00:02:23,518
I should take a break.

23
00:02:23,601 --> 00:02:24,936
Clean that up.

24
00:02:25,019 --> 00:02:26,020
I'm sorry.

25
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:32,026
Didn't you order a cake
for Da-jeong's birthday tomorrow?

26
00:02:32,694 --> 00:02:34,070
Her birthday is in two days.

27
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:36,489
What? That's Young-do's birthday too.

28
00:02:37,073 --> 00:02:38,950
Did you talk to Young-do on the phone?

29
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:41,411
Mr. Ju? No. Why?

30
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:43,121
What? It's nothing.

31
00:02:43,204 --> 00:02:44,664
Did you go to the bathroom?

32
00:02:44,747 --> 00:02:46,457
What if you need to go while driving?

33
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:49,919
-Mom, do you think I'm still a kid?
-Yes. You always are to me.

34
00:02:51,087 --> 00:02:52,255
I'll call you in Seoul.

35
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:54,716
You have to go to work right away,
so don't bother.

36
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:56,634
Eat something if you have time for that.

37
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:57,927
Okay.

38
00:02:58,011 --> 00:02:59,596
Off you go. I'm busy.

39
00:03:00,096 --> 00:03:01,180
-Bye.
-Okay.

40
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:03,266
Bye.

41
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:21,284
Gosh, it's true.

42
00:03:21,868 --> 00:03:23,995
March 29th is May 10th
on the lunar calendar this year.

43
00:03:24,078 --> 00:03:26,873
The stars aligned, but why are they
still not dating properly?

44
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:29,125
It's like a movie.

45
00:03:29,208 --> 00:03:31,794
Even movies shouldn't drag on like this.

46
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:34,756
It's time for me to step up.

47
00:03:34,839 --> 00:03:36,341
Whatever it is, don't do it.

48
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:38,801
What we need is a hidden camera prank.

49
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,804
You know the catfish effect, right?
That competition makes people better.

50
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:43,431
-Care to hear my plan?
-No, thanks.

51
00:03:43,514 --> 00:03:46,601
First, we need Eun-ha's help.

52
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:55,360
DOCTOR'S OFFICE

53
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:56,778
PSYCHIATRIST JU YOUNG-DO

54
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:07,580
She'll push him to the wall.

55
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:11,376
Why… Why does she have to do such a thing?

56
00:04:21,552 --> 00:04:22,887
I hoped I would

57
00:04:23,596 --> 00:04:26,015
win your heart this way.

58
00:04:30,895 --> 00:04:32,355
I'm yours.

59
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:40,321
Upon seeing that,
Ms. Kang will be blinded by jealousy.

60
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:41,990
Where does she appear from?

61
00:04:42,573 --> 00:04:44,784
I don't know.
From behind the wall or something.

62
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:47,036
You really didn't put
much effort into the plan.

63
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:53,293
First of all, I doubt Ms. Park
would agree to do that.

64
00:04:53,376 --> 00:04:56,379
Even if she did,
Mr. Ju wouldn't react that way.

65
00:04:58,548 --> 00:04:59,841
I hoped I would

66
00:05:00,591 --> 00:05:02,760
win your heart this way.

67
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:12,312
Well…

68
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:16,649
Seeing that you cornered and held me down
while confessing your love,

69
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:19,152
you must find pleasure
in controlling others.

70
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:22,155
That could be considered
a sadistic personality.

71
00:05:22,822 --> 00:05:26,367
I could try to understand this
by blaming the media

72
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:29,329
for making such actions look romantic.

73
00:05:30,371 --> 00:05:33,916
But if that's not the case
and you simply find joy in doing this,

74
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:37,378
I think you should receive therapy.

75
00:05:39,213 --> 00:05:41,632
She's right. I don't think
Eun-ha should do that.

76
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:44,886
Instead, Cheol-do should ask Da-jeong out.

77
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:52,393
He'll approach her
as a completely changed man.

78
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:53,394
You are…

79
00:05:55,646 --> 00:05:56,522
inside my heart.

80
00:05:57,106 --> 00:05:59,776
I see. In that case…

81
00:06:00,777 --> 00:06:01,778
Knock, knock.

82
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:05,406
Are you in there, Ms. Kang?

83
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:09,744
And Young-do sees that

84
00:06:09,827 --> 00:06:12,371
-and brushes his teeth in fury.
-Hello.

85
00:06:12,455 --> 00:06:14,582
Why would he be brushing his teeth there?

86
00:06:14,665 --> 00:06:17,543
I don't know. Maybe he likes
the toothpaste that she uses.

87
00:06:18,169 --> 00:06:20,213
You guys have terrible imaginations.

88
00:06:20,296 --> 00:06:21,839
Wasn't the last one decent?

89
00:06:21,923 --> 00:06:23,257
Not one bit.

90
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:27,136
If Mr. Park did that,
Da-jeong would definitely…

91
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:33,935
You are…

92
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:36,813
inside my heart.

93
00:06:37,396 --> 00:06:38,272
Let go.

94
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:42,443
-You are--
-I said, let go.

95
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:43,444
I'm sorry, ma'am.

96
00:06:54,956 --> 00:06:57,125
And he's a terrible runner.

97
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:01,838
What kind of cake should we get?

98
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:03,798
Young-do shouldn't have anything
too sweet.

99
00:07:04,757 --> 00:07:06,884
I wonder what kind of cake Da-jeong likes.

100
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:12,223
The person you are trying to reach
is unavailable. Please leave a message…

101
00:07:13,391 --> 00:07:14,350
He's not picking up?

102
00:07:16,394 --> 00:07:18,980
Just look ahead and focus on driving.

103
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:22,775
It must be one of these four reasons.

104
00:07:23,359 --> 00:07:26,487
He's arrested, mourning, sick,

105
00:07:26,571 --> 00:07:28,156
or doesn't care about you.

106
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:30,491
Working, showering,

107
00:07:30,575 --> 00:07:33,202
sleeping, watching a movie…

108
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:34,328
Maybe one of them.

109
00:07:39,876 --> 00:07:43,588
I'm sorry. I was too busy
to answer your call.

110
00:07:44,338 --> 00:07:46,090
Did you arrive in Seoul?

111
00:07:46,174 --> 00:07:48,050
We're still on our way.

112
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,219
Make sure to eat
no matter how busy you are.

113
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:52,096
You too.

114
00:07:56,684 --> 00:07:58,853
We got the ultrasound
and angiography results.

115
00:07:58,936 --> 00:08:00,438
Thankfully, they're clean.

116
00:08:00,521 --> 00:08:02,148
It's bacterial pneumonia, isn't it?

117
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:03,900
You were reinfected.

118
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:07,028
Maybe it was from one of your outpatients.

119
00:08:08,362 --> 00:08:10,281
I should stay here for a few days, right?

120
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:13,534
After the biopsy, I need to--

121
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:14,911
Go out?

122
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:19,165
I can't ask my therapy patients
to get therapy elsewhere.

123
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:22,627
And one of my patients today
is in a critical--

124
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:24,170
Haven't you learned your lesson?

125
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:28,925
Your patients must be important to you
just like you are to me.

126
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:30,676
But you should know what's more important.

127
00:08:31,761 --> 00:08:32,762
Young-do.

128
00:08:33,846 --> 00:08:35,431
Did you cut down on your work?

129
00:08:36,974 --> 00:08:40,061
You're still on TV and helping the cops,
aren't you?

130
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:49,654
You can't be a psychiatrist
if you're going to keep this up.

131
00:08:49,737 --> 00:08:53,199
You're carrying all your patients
and even the dead ones on your shoulders,

132
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:54,909
and forcing yourself to endure it.

133
00:08:55,952 --> 00:08:58,079
You almost got in an accident today.

134
00:08:58,621 --> 00:09:00,498
What if you ran over someone?

135
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:03,668
What if your girlfriend was
in your car with you?

136
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:12,677
-I can borrow some props.
-This isn't an opening ceremony.

137
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,720
We should have garlands on the rooftop.

138
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:17,098
Gosh. Is this a field day or something?

139
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:20,017
Then we'll line up some candles--

140
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:21,519
That's a violation of law.

141
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:23,104
Then how about some flowers?

142
00:09:23,187 --> 00:09:25,439
Da-jeong will detest them.

143
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:29,277
Then let's change our cake
to a two-tier one.

144
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,487
-It's a joint birthday.
-This isn't a wedding.

145
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:33,656
Then we'll place some refreshments
on plates--

146
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:35,157
For a community meeting?

147
00:09:35,992 --> 00:09:38,452
You're not letting me do anything.

148
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:40,538
Don't do anything. Just don't.

149
00:09:40,621 --> 00:09:41,455
It's Young-do.

150
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:45,293
-Hey, we're here--
-Ha-neul.

151
00:09:45,793 --> 00:09:47,878
I have a favor to ask.

152
00:09:48,963 --> 00:09:50,047
Sure. What is it?

153
00:09:51,716 --> 00:09:53,467
I think my car got towed

154
00:09:54,468 --> 00:09:56,762
because I had to rush over
to the hospital.

155
00:09:59,557 --> 00:10:01,267
No, I'm hospitalized.

156
00:10:01,809 --> 00:10:03,352
I'll be here for a few days.

157
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,313
Then is it…

158
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:08,566
quite serious?

159
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:13,321
I'll be fine.

160
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:16,449
But I'd like you
to keep it a secret for now.

161
00:10:17,658 --> 00:10:20,328
I don't want Da-jeong to know.

162
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:24,790
Sure. Don't worry about anything.

163
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,627
All right, then. Bye.

164
00:11:04,288 --> 00:11:06,749
He went back to that hotel?
Is he allowed to do that?

165
00:11:06,832 --> 00:11:07,958
I mean, that's…

166
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:12,171
But then again, it's not illegal.

167
00:11:12,254 --> 00:11:13,673
We can make our next move

168
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:17,009
only if that server company hands over
the surveillance camera footage.

169
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:18,886
Why are they refusing?

170
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:22,348
They demanded a warrant,
so what choice do we have?

171
00:11:23,265 --> 00:11:25,476
But the footage will give us a result

172
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:27,269
more quickly than forensics.

173
00:11:27,353 --> 00:11:29,313
But this is a murder case for God's sake.

174
00:11:30,314 --> 00:11:32,441
Oh, I was just on the phone.

175
00:11:33,275 --> 00:11:34,819
They sent the footage.

176
00:11:35,569 --> 00:11:38,072
What do you mean? They wanted a warrant.

177
00:11:38,155 --> 00:11:41,283
-Out of the blue?
-They even came all the way here.

178
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:43,411
They agreed to cooperate with us.

179
00:11:44,036 --> 00:11:45,663
What are they trying to pull?

180
00:11:45,746 --> 00:11:47,790
-Let's see it. Hurry up.
-Yes, sir.

181
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:25,536
Yes, sir. I'm listening.
I'm still in the parking lot.

182
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:26,495
Hello?

183
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:32,168
Hello? Ian?

184
00:12:33,043 --> 00:12:34,003
Ian!

185
00:13:08,329 --> 00:13:10,289
You impudent bastard.

186
00:13:11,665 --> 00:13:14,543
I asked you to get me a lawyer,
but you sent me thugs?

187
00:13:17,129 --> 00:13:18,547
Once you wake up,

188
00:13:20,257 --> 00:13:21,300
I'm going…

189
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:25,387
to ask you one question.

190
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:28,807
After that,

191
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:32,478
I'll let you be reunited
with your twin brother.

192
00:13:49,578 --> 00:13:51,580
Ian.

193
00:13:52,206 --> 00:13:54,124
Ian.

194
00:14:05,427 --> 00:14:06,512
See that?

195
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:08,973
She knew about this camera.

196
00:14:09,723 --> 00:14:11,183
Maybe she put it there.

197
00:14:12,393 --> 00:14:13,602
She went there every day.

198
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:15,312
Did she know she was going to die?

199
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:17,356
She was probably keeping an eye on Chase.

200
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,152
Ian.

201
00:14:54,643 --> 00:14:58,522
WON AND BAEK LAWYER KWON JUNG-HYEON

202
00:15:23,088 --> 00:15:25,424
This will be much more entertaining

203
00:15:27,176 --> 00:15:30,346
than trying to find out
if that 18-year-old boy was you

204
00:15:32,389 --> 00:15:33,766
or your dead brother.

205
00:15:46,528 --> 00:15:48,572
Now, both of you twins

206
00:15:49,823 --> 00:15:52,660
have become murderers.

207
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:11,845
First, we need to find out
why that company gladly

208
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:15,599
handed over this footage
when they had demanded a warrant before.

209
00:16:15,683 --> 00:16:19,269
Second, who benefits the most
from this footage being revealed?

210
00:16:19,353 --> 00:16:20,187
It's Ian Chase.

211
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,107
We need to find out who's helping him.

212
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:25,109
WANTED FOR MURDER

213
00:16:37,287 --> 00:16:39,081
You're in a pickle, aren't you?

214
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:43,585
A woman was killed.

215
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:44,670
Exactly.

216
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:48,632
I'm glad there was a camera there.

217
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:53,178
I never thought
it would be used like this.

218
00:16:56,473 --> 00:16:58,726
You're not shaken
by something like this, are you?

219
00:17:05,649 --> 00:17:10,654
The chairman's surgery is upcoming.
You should've been more careful.

220
00:17:11,363 --> 00:17:13,323
How could you drink it without checking?

221
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:17,703
You're just like your brother.

222
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:22,624
What do you mean?

223
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:25,169
He had a drink, passed out,
and woke up with a knife.

224
00:17:26,754 --> 00:17:27,963
Right.

225
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:32,801
I'm the only one
who saw the footage of him.

226
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:37,097
The camera's been there
since he lived there?

227
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:39,641
I had to find what you cherished
to find your weakness,

228
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:43,187
but you didn't have any.

229
00:17:44,229 --> 00:17:47,858
He was your only family member,
so I looked into him.

230
00:17:49,234 --> 00:17:50,486
I'm asking…

231
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:54,656
how long that camera has been there.

232
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:00,829
What do you want to see?

233
00:18:02,456 --> 00:18:04,374
The day before his death?

234
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:06,293
Or the day of?

235
00:18:16,386 --> 00:18:18,097
We'll talk again after you watch it.

236
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,307
We'll have a lot to talk about.

237
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:33,862
WANTED FOR MURDER

238
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:35,572
I should've killed them all.

239
00:18:37,574 --> 00:18:38,575
All of them.

240
00:18:42,037 --> 00:18:43,622
I should've killed them all.

241
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,459
Every single one of them.

242
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:53,632
Turn your headlights off.

243
00:18:56,927 --> 00:18:58,178
How rude.

244
00:19:52,649 --> 00:19:53,483
Is it confirmed?

245
00:19:54,902 --> 00:19:57,946
-Did you find out anything new?
-Ahn Ga-yeong and Patrick?

246
00:19:58,030 --> 00:19:59,239
What an odd couple.

247
00:19:59,323 --> 00:20:00,866
EXCLUSIVE: AHN GA-YEONG AND PATRICK DATING
DESPITE A 10-YEAR AGE GAP

248
00:20:00,949 --> 00:20:02,492
I'm not sure about that though…

249
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:03,493
She's a divorcée?

250
00:20:04,077 --> 00:20:05,537
-It's a 10-year gap.
-No way.

251
00:20:05,621 --> 00:20:07,331
Could this be real?

252
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:09,458
They're really an odd match.

253
00:20:09,541 --> 00:20:10,876
It might be.

254
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:13,629
Does this mean
today's shooting is canceled?

255
00:20:14,379 --> 00:20:16,757
Ahn Ga-yeong and Patrick
are ten years apart.

256
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:20,219
If my boyfriend was ten years my junior,
he'd still be in high school.

257
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:23,555
That must be why I'm still single.

258
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:26,058
He's still a minor
who's preparing for his exams.

259
00:20:26,141 --> 00:20:27,684
That's why we haven't met.

260
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:32,940
Yu-kyeong, ask the reporters
one by one to leave

261
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:35,776
so that they won't inconvenience
the hotel guests.

262
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:37,819
